1 dist rict's general fund a stipend of Twenty-five Dollars ($25.00)
2 for each regular, special or adjourned meeting of the board of
3 education that he or she attends, but not for more than four
4 meetings in any calendar month.
5 E. 1. Unless otherwise provided by law, a board of education
6 may submit an Affidavit of Board Action to the State Department of
7 Education in lieu of approved board minutes to provide proof of an
8 action approved or taken at a board meeting. Such affidavit shall
9 be signed and sworn by the applicable personnel as provided in
10 paragraph 2 of this subsection. The State Department of Education
11 shall accept a signed Affidavit of Board Action as certification
12 that the district board has approved or taken a specific action at a
13 board meeting. Nothing in this subsection shall exempt a board of
14 education from keeping minutes of a meeting in accordance with
15 Section 312 of Title 25 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
16 2. The Affidavit of Board Action described in paragraph 1 of
17 this subsection shall include:
18 a. the county or district code,
19 b. the name of the school district,
20 c. the date of the board meeting,
21 d. the agenda item number approved,
22 e. a summary of the action approved,
